17/09/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- On Tuesday (16 September), parliament's committee for legislation endorsed a bilateral agreement with the United States which exempts citizens from the jurisdiction of the International Criminal Court.
Parliament is now scheduled to debate and ratify the accord next week.
In other news Tuesday, Prime Minister Branko Crvenkovski said he would send a letter to EU security chief Javier Solana next week, requesting that an advisory mission, consisting of about 100 experts, be dispatched to Macedonia after the rapid reaction force Concordia's mission ends in December.
(MIA, A1 TV - 17/09/03)
